WEBVTT

00:00:00.190 --> 00:00:02.370
<v Teacher>Okay so we are getting to the final section</v>

00:00:02.370 --> 00:00:04.950
of this course to prepare for your examination.

00:00:04.950 --> 00:00:08.000
But first I want to give you a quick note about distractors.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.430
So you will find many services in the answers

00:00:10.430 --> 00:00:12.680
of the questions in the exam that we haven't seen yet

00:00:12.680 --> 00:00:14.960
in this course and they are called distractors.

00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:18.380
To be fair there are over 200 AWS services out there,

00:00:18.380 --> 00:00:20.870
and I cannot cover them all in this course,

00:00:20.870 --> 00:00:21.790
you will be overloaded

00:00:21.790 --> 00:00:23.690
and it will not make any sense to you.

00:00:23.690 --> 00:00:26.700
So for example these services can be Quicksight, Cognito,

00:00:26.700 --> 00:00:29.970
AppStreams, Server Migration Service, et cetera, et cetera.

00:00:29.970 --> 00:00:31.870
In my opinion and as a teacher,

00:00:31.870 --> 00:00:34.220
it's my due diligence to make sure that I have covered

00:00:34.220 --> 00:00:37.230
all the services that from my research and experience

00:00:37.230 --> 00:00:40.510
you will get questions on at the exam.

00:00:40.510 --> 00:00:43.010
Now you can go out there and practice.

00:00:43.010 --> 00:00:45.540
And if you see a service not covered by my course,

00:00:45.540 --> 00:00:47.550
but in someone else's practice exam,

00:00:47.550 --> 00:00:49.920
it's not my responsibility, in my opinion

00:00:49.920 --> 00:00:52.270
that service should not be in the exam

00:00:52.270 --> 00:00:53.940
and it should not be in a practice exam,

00:00:53.940 --> 00:00:57.930
so I intentionally left it out, but don't panic okay?

00:00:57.930 --> 00:01:00.930
This is normal you will find questions that will mention

00:01:00.930 --> 00:01:02.910
services that you've never seen before.

00:01:02.910 --> 00:01:05.530
But again, they're distractors they should never be

00:01:05.530 --> 00:01:06.810
the right answer.

00:01:06.810 --> 00:01:09.490
So try to focus on the service that I've talked to you

00:01:09.490 --> 00:01:13.000
in this course, which are more than 40 services anyway,

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:16.090
and people don't worry, pass the exam with flying colors

00:01:16.090 --> 00:01:17.280
with my course.

00:01:17.280 --> 00:01:21.160
Now, if you actually do see a service that is an answer

00:01:21.160 --> 00:01:22.830
at the exam and you're certain of that,

00:01:22.830 --> 00:01:25.610
but I did not cover in my course, please let me know

00:01:25.610 --> 00:01:27.690
I will of course update the course,

00:01:27.690 --> 00:01:31.410
and am not aiming for you to get 700 out of 1,000,

00:01:31.410 --> 00:01:34.410
am aiming for you to have over 900 out of 1,000

00:01:34.410 --> 00:01:35.243
for the exam.

00:01:35.243 --> 00:01:37.900
So even if one question is not covered by my course,

00:01:37.900 --> 00:01:39.740
you will be fine for passing your exam,

00:01:39.740 --> 00:01:42.160
you will let me know and then I will adapt the course.

00:01:42.160 --> 00:01:42.993
This is it.

00:01:42.993 --> 00:01:44.660
So this was a quick note on the distractors.

00:01:44.660 --> 00:01:47.410
I will see you in the next lecture to see where we are.